@page
@model Webority.Web.GovIndia.Pages.Services.CitizenAppsModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Citizen Web & App Development for Government India";
    ViewData["Description"] = "Offline-first, multilingual, GIGW 3.0 / WCAG 2.1 AA citizen web and mobile apps for Indian government schemes — proven in zero-connectivity tribal field conditions.";
    ViewData["ActiveNav"] = "services";
    ViewData["BodyClass"] = "services-page";
}
<!-- Hero -->
  <section class="egov-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="egov-hero-content">
        <h1>Citizen Web &amp; App Development for Government India</h1>
        <p class="egov-hero-lead">Mobile and web applications serving as the public face of government schemes — offline-first, multilingual, GIGW 3.0 compliant, and proven in the most challenging field conditions across India.</p>
        <p class="svc-hero-standards">Offline-First Architecture   ·   12+ Indian Languages   ·   WCAG 2.1 AA · GIGW 3.0</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Deliver -->
  <section class="egov-band">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="egov-band-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="egov-eyebrow">What We Deliver</span>
          <h2 class="egov-h2">Reaching Every Citizen — In Every Language</h2>
          <p class="copy">We build mobile and web applications that serve as the public face of government schemes — designed for accessibility, offline functionality, multilingual support, and deployment at scale across India’s diverse geography.</p>
          <ul class="egov-checklist">
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> Citizen service portals (web + mobile)</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> Field officer apps with offline sync</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> Scheme enrollment &amp; beneficiary management</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> UMANG-compatible service modules</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> Aadhaar eKYC &amp; DigiLocker integrated</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> Multilingual — 12+ Indian languages</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="egov-btn-row">
            <a asp-page="/Contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-glow btn-md"><span class="btn-glow-label">Discuss Your Requirements</span><svg class="btn-glow-arrow" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg></a>
            <a asp-page="/CaseStudies" class="btn btn-outline btn-md">View Projects</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="egov-ref-panel">
          <span class="egov-eyebrow">Reference Projects</span>
          <!-- TODO-WG: each public-sector reference below must have approved public listing before publishing. -->
          <ul class="egov-ref-list">
            <li class="egov-ref-item">
              <span class="egov-ref-logo"><img src="/images/logos/gov/Sickle Scan logo 64px.svg" alt="Sickle Scan — Ministry of Tribal Affairs" loading="lazy" /></span>
              <span>
                <p class="egov-ref-name">Sickle Scan — Ministry of Tribal Affairs</p>
                <p class="egov-ref-proj">National Sickle Cell Mission · Offline-first · 8+ languages · ASHA worker UX</p>
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Capabilities -->
  <section class="egov-build">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="egov-build-head">
        <span class="egov-eyebrow">Capabilities</span>
        <h2 class="egov-h2">Advanced Features in Every Government App We Build</h2>
        <p>High-demand capabilities that define quality in government mobile and web applications.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="egov-build-grid">
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 11.5a8.38 8.38 0 0 1-8.5 8.5 8.38 8.38 0 0 1-3.8-.9L3 21l1.9-5.7a8.38 8.38 0 0 1-.9-3.8 8.5 8.5 0 0 1 17 0z"/></svg></span>
          <h3>AI-Powered Citizen Chatbot</h3>
          <p>Multilingual voice and text assistant handling FAQs, scheme eligibility checks, and grievance filing — available 24×7 on web and WhatsApp.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M18 8A6 6 0 0 0 6 8c0 7-3 9-3 9h18s-3-2-3-9"/><path d="M13.73 21a2 2 0 0 1-3.46 0"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Smart Push Notifications &amp; Alerts</h3>
          <p>Targeted scheme updates, application status alerts, and deadline reminders — reaching citizens via app, SMS, and WhatsApp.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="1" y1="1" x2="23" y2="23"/><path d="M16.72 11.06A10.94 10.94 0 0 1 19 12.55"/><path d="M5 12.55a10.94 10.94 0 0 1 5.17-2.39"/><path d="M10.71 5.05A16 16 0 0 1 22.58 9"/><path d="M1.42 9a15.91 15.91 0 0 1 4.7-2.88"/><path d="M8.53 16.11a6 6 0 0 1 6.95 0"/><line x1="12" y1="20" x2="12.01" y2="20"/></svg></span>
          <h3>100% Offline Functionality</h3>
          <p>Full app operation without internet — data captured offline syncs automatically when connectivity is restored. Proven in tribal deployments.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="2" y="4" width="20" height="16" rx="2"/><circle cx="9" cy="10" r="2"/><path d="M15 8h4M15 12h4M5 16h14"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Aadhaar &amp; DigiLocker Integration</h3>
          <p>Seamless eKYC verification, document fetch from DigiLocker, and UPI payment integration — zero paper, zero queue.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="4" r="1.6"/><path d="M5 7h14M12 7v6m0 0-3 7m3-7 3 7"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Accessibility-First Design</h3>
          <p>Screen-reader compatible, high-contrast modes, adjustable font sizes, and voice navigation — GIGW 3.0 and WCAG 2.1 AA compliant.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0 1 18 0z"/><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Geo-Tagging &amp; Field Verification</h3>
          <p>GPS-stamped field submissions, photo capture with location metadata, and real-time officer tracking for programme monitoring.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Certifications -->
  <section class="egov-certs">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="sect-head">
        <span class="egov-eyebrow">Government &amp; Public Sector</span>
        <h2 class="egov-h2">Certifications</h2>
      </div>
      <!-- TODO-WG: confirm the exact list of held certifications; replace any seal below with the real certificate. -->
      <div class="cert-seals-row">
        <div class="cert-seal-card"><div class="cert-seal-img-wrap"><img class="cert-seal-img" src="/images/credentials/cmmi-l5.png" alt="CMMI Level 5 certified" loading="lazy" /></div><div class="cert-seal-card-name">CMMI Level 5</div></div>
        <div class="cert-seal-card"><div class="cert-seal-img-wrap"><img class="cert-seal-img" src="/images/credentials/iso-27001-2022.png" alt="ISO 27001:2022 certified" loading="lazy" /></div><div class="cert-seal-card-name">Information Security</div></div>
        <div class="cert-seal-card"><div class="cert-seal-img-wrap"><img class="cert-seal-img" src="/images/credentials/iso-9001-2015.png" alt="ISO 9001:2015 certified" loading="lazy" /></div><div class="cert-seal-card-name">Quality Management</div></div>
        <div class="cert-seal-card"><div class="cert-seal-img-wrap"><img class="cert-seal-img" src="/images/credentials/iso-20000-2018.png" alt="ISO 20000:2018 certified" loading="lazy" /></div><div class="cert-seal-card-name">IT Service Management</div></div>
        <div class="cert-seal-card"><div class="cert-seal-img-wrap"><img class="cert-seal-img" src="/images/logos/gov/Start up logo.svg" alt="DPIIT — Startup India recognised" loading="lazy" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.parentNode.classList.add('reg-card-logo--fallback'); this.parentNode.setAttribute('aria-hidden','true'); this.parentNode.textContent='DPIIT';" /></div><div class="cert-seal-card-name">Startup India / DPIIT</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="egov-faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="sect-head">

        <h2 class="egov-h2">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      </div>
      <!-- TODO-WG: verify each Q&A pairing and all compliance/client claims (ISO version, certifications, named bodies) before publishing. -->
      <div class="faq-wrap">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">How do Webority’s citizen apps work without internet connectivity?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Offline-first architecture is a core specialisation for Webority Technologies. Our field officer applications use local-first data storage with sync-when-connected architecture — the app remains fully functional in areas with zero internet connectivity and automatically synchronises data when connectivity is restored. This is proven in our Sickle Scan deployment for ASHA workers in remote tribal districts under the Ministry of Tribal Affairs’ National Sickle Cell Mission, and the BEE Field Officer App for market surveillance across State Designated Agencies.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Do Webority’s government apps support multiple Indian languages including tribal dialects?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Citizen app development for government requires support for 12+ Indian languages including low-literacy UX patterns, offline-first architecture for rural and tribal deployments, integration with India Stack (Aadhaar, DigiLocker, UPI), and DPDP Act 2023-compliant data handling. These requirements require government-native engineering from the first line of code. Webority has proven this in the most demanding conditions: Sickle Scan for the Ministry of Tribal Affairs, deployed in zero-connectivity tribal districts.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Can Webority’s citizen apps be procured through the GeM marketplace?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>GIGW 3.0 (Guidelines for Indian Government Websites) compliance and WCAG 2.1 Level AA accessibility are baseline requirements — built into our development process from the first design sprint, not verified at the end. This includes screen reader compatibility, keyboard navigation, sufficient colour contrast, multilingual content structure, and MeitY mobile application guidelines compliance. Departments receive a GIGW 3.0 compliance report and WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility audit as standard project deliverables.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA strip -->
  <section class="egov-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Building a citizen-facing platform?</h2>
      <p>Tell us about the scheme, the languages, and the field conditions — we’ll design for the citizen at the edge of the network.</p>
      <a asp-page="/Contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-glow btn-md"><span class="btn-glow-label">Contact Us</span><svg class="btn-glow-arrow" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg></a>
    </div>
  </section>

@section HeadStyles {
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/pages/service-citizen-apps.css" />
}
